 stack that does not tie up cpu_resources with its 1 hour (3600,000)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Y@7!fII^f~o`7v)~jf#z"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="W6Z^dPTDCeg8sxg%Vi(."><field name="TEXT">Also the 'if(false)' mini-stacks will be skipped by cpu, for further non-resource burdening</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="Pe(4.X^j+CcP.E$O_c0#"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="~Abx,S.NGa/twK~Cq]pH"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id="IyY2%ax;!+[Od!__9]X}"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="]jXjypzfC!ltLY{;G*PN"><field name="TEXT">Staff: Very Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="T;+Uj!Y#ASO.+kXA(I%d"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="oL6UN92un(;Dfb~~r)dK"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="ULi?]ESX5|m!3ufurzsU"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="jT_2|$j~!HrvfF28)L-M"><field name="TEXT">Levels 1, 2, 2.1</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="K=Km*.kx{*^F;:jV5%KC"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="hCC7}R#jgO,hT0+^B/uo"><field name="TEXT">* Level 1: Hardcoded Static via Actual_Numbers for MotorPower%</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="jmlkuKQe94JbSiH}P,J}"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="`~a8c0|R|Vz,6}rysptW"><field name="TEXT">* Level 2: Softcoded Dynamic via Variables/Constants for MotorPower% </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="chl`lPh2`(M0}T*t(0kA"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="jwv*fU~DC$5+xDE:J*nL"><field name="TEXT">* Level 2.1 Add Controller_Joystick * Level 2.2 Add Gear 3 (90%?)</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="|ZW*$+Y|~_p$:`7m,W=8"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id=",IQ9Y@^c4)CwZF~)N1h8"><field name="TEXT">Basic Comment_Colors Usage:: Black: Very Big Picture, Blue: Big Picture, Green: Following Block_Code Moddable, Orange: Question/TODO, Magenta: Special Multi-Purpose </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="%TF6MBp6a6Tbr6q$o)RV"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="TElC1?g`%9Mem*kOP=W="><field name="TEXT">micro:bit Ver2 Warning during Download is Ignorable Yet Courteously Helpful</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="=H49QyS?YW]pNCsNU.vO"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="4ujnZ?bBc;_J_zn-heG4"><field name="TEXT">'if_then' mini-stacks useful for modular 3-D code select/duplicate/move/delete</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="94W85P^Z?wYm:Lqg}l{I"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="!@Q-abN9PYLh4)oe[qHL"><field name="TEXT">Light_Gray Functions non-editable (backend staff-use code only)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="yM@-O-T`mZ_gk.xDvcpA"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="a)lYI=U?kKRM^7xnHqZO"><field name="TEXT">For Group_CHannel_# (Bot_Id): Propose: 1-10 Staff Use, 11-99 Student Use</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="O}@R}vPd#4hy}9oCB:/H"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="ghY1.[yCW;UNs%Sj|1?D"><field name="TEXT">SW Reset: Long_Press Logo for 3 sec min</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="vB3z5ckQL${BIaDq-ygJ"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="@~qqE!WKeR{)f[#v4JQV"><field name="TEXT">Built-in Diagnostic Test: Short_Press Logo for 1 sec max</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="oRC(`TPE|*nWTujW^CFU"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="(1M_dJ#p1PVcTrL+O;y:"><field name="TEXT">'Blocks' Window homes 'on start'_stack as top_left corner of editor_screen, until 'on start' is moved below, then next stack to right presides</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="iwIelyHOba/{|?Evjw.a"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="jD;h4K7`ea93D0-Q[|-s"><field name="TEXT">All These Levels are Intermediate Level Coding due to Networking Pairing Involved.  Basic Diagnostic Servo_Motors (Autonomoous) is Beginner Level.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="zyIPU-ANlg$ZDWy:-(Na"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="byfTej%Xtd)!@|;cqJoh"><field name="TEXT">This Intermediate Level Network_Pairing has 1sec_Lag Response Time; The Other Advanced Level Network_Pairing has Real_Time Response Time.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="sgktct^Nz0=/vW/?YP8t"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="gF`j=q~@=w.L]m7/*man"><field name="TEXT">For Level 1, can keep 'Forward: set manual_servo_motors' Block functional, yet reset to 0 all other 'set manual_servo_motors' Blocks for Discovery Learning</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="[+LOb7{Fy)f$@_l;E9Y4"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="y1S3*`_Wck12eG%Y#^u8"><field name="TEXT">If duplicate stacks exist, then the highest stack is active and others are non_active</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="controls_if" id="e9RnB(*5!YAVzp!cX)Zx"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="wm5xL;tc5^GxoEUckq[M"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id="~]Of8]D4;/L!]ZxT7{/!"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="}SYE5Fm5%vtCeM0o#W=h"><field name="TEXT">Staff: Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="@9.z-D:cX]FJO.@170B@"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="WCyYi}uZb{Zu@nZeEe0O"><field name="TEXT">Upon open file, Editor zooms in on closest stack to right of original_origin from project_creation</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="vo-#;MFJ{W@s4Ys03o:~"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="oTG-Lvya]iVAodV4^@`]"><field name="TEXT">Semantic Naming prefers '_' vs. '-' since latter can be conufused with minus_sign</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="`1-8w8c,DYA,!FV9,gg$"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="g*$T?Dr8FhB7?!L10YME"><field name="TEXT">'every 360000 ms' (1 hour) Stacks can be ignored, esp w/ 'if false' embedded</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="7H}*9~}pEm[5,4=##afe"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="|RQy-liWwoEAYzLeE`jg"><field name="TEXT">Avoid using 'show leds' Block since will cause lag &amp; degrade real-time response</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="9K9jq)yd[(DjQ)Z@ch0="><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="/Iex7j`vAdf8G4{hBT[@"><field name="TEXT">Seems like 'signficant' changes to JavaScript can activate 'format code', rearrange stacks to original position</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="g3wN9daA]-=H)jlhsS^i"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="1^KNR1wt~DrM@_AveWi:"><field name="TEXT">Important 'system' variables are 1) _system_Hw_DeviceType__* (Hw=Hardware) and 2) _system_Sw_ModeState__* (Sw=Software)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Pyy:K~GMhFh${4=09qx]"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="~giH[3R(0~Q;N2.D`w.f"><field name="TEXT">If Buttons C-F for Gears/Misc, Maybe 'Logo Up/Down' for 'Servo_Arm Up/Down'</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="_:qSzQ!XgJ_XHbjKkf|C"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="ejO|R=juX~Pr7H^v6GVj"><field name="TEXT">'Rotatedisplay' could be used on Bot's Led_Screen, but causes light flickering on bottom row, so maybe avoid</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="t;YpmQ1:S6)5d?dei[r5"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="*i.OtI0.me2f.EZBvKqW"><field name="TEXT">Reliable/Faster Response If Screen_Led_Graphics After Important Action Blocks Above</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="xpcmxU.WJM/_hR=mj*Rn"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="B!~$bb~0EcaMg5CzT@r@"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="ePCB1DfoZyD2yEM1mCl^"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="!)?XI%,iWF82btw3ELjy"><field name="TEXT">Main upgrade from Lv1 to Lv2 is replacing cpu_laggy 'show leds' block with cpu_fast 'plox x _ y _' block, such as below: </field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="+.*DlrXDW2%o;W#!nMJq"><mutation elseif="4" else="1"></mutation><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="R/91+%;fPgqU~Y09gy`F"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></sh